e economic model that it had been designed to overcome. It explores the phantasmatic and absurd dimensions of the transformation of social reality under conditions of global capitalism, deconstructing the utopian fantasies of the state, and drawing attention to the eruption of insurgent utopias staged by those with nothing left to lose.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aSustainable developmentzAmazon River Valley. 0aSustainable developmentzEcuador. 0aUtopiaszEcuador. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / South America.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300262933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300262933/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles